                <h2 class="h3 fw-bold mb-4">Legal Technology Modernization</h2>
                <p class="lead">Upgrade aging systems without disrupting firm operations. I modernize incrementally to minimize risk.</p>

                <p>Law firms often run critical systems that are years behind current technology—but can't afford downtime during migration. I specialize in gradual modernization that keeps everything running while moving to modern platforms.</p>

                <h4 class="mt-4 mb-3">Modernization Services:</h4>
                <ul class="mb-4">
                    <li><strong>Platform Upgrades:</strong> Moving from legacy .NET Framework to modern .NET</li>
                    <li><strong>Cloud Migration:</strong> Moving on-premises systems to Azure with proper security</li>
                    <li><strong>Integration Updates:</strong> Modernizing connections to DMS, time and billing, and other firm systems</li>
                    <li><strong>Performance Optimization:</strong> Making slow systems fast again</li>
                    <li><strong>Security Hardening:</strong> Bringing legacy systems up to current security standards</li>
                </ul>

                <p>I understand that firm technology can't have extended downtime. All modernization work is planned for minimal disruption. More on <a href="/services/legacy-systems">legacy system modernization</a>.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

